# Implementation Plan - UX Improvements

## Goal Description
Enhance the user experience of the SGQ application by introducing a professional "Landing Page" (Dashboard) and applying global visual polish (removing gridlines, standardizing zoom). This aims to create a "Wow" factor and make the tool feel like a standalone application.

## User Review Required
> [!NOTE]
> The 'Accueil' sheet will be the new entry point. Ensure 'TDM' and 'TDM-Suivi' sheets are the correct destinations for the buttons.

## Proposed Changes

### UI/Interface Layer

#### [MODIFY] [modSGQInterface.bas](file:///c%3A/VBA/SGQ%201.65/vba-files/Module/modSGQInterface.bas)
- **New Procedure `SetupDashboard`**:
    - Check if 'Accueil' sheet exists, create if not.
    - Clear existing content/shapes.
    - Set styling: No gridlines, background color (e.g., rigid white or soft gray), Zoom 100%.
    - **Draw Buttons**:
        - "Système de Gestion de la Qualité" -> Links to Sheet 'TDM'.
        - "Activités de suivi" -> Links to Sheet 'TDM-Suivi'.
        - Gear Icon (Shape) -> Links to a settings macro (placeholder or existing).
- **New Procedure `ApplyVisualPolish`**:
    - Iterate through all worksheets.
    - set `ActiveWindow.DisplayGridlines = False`.
    - set `ActiveWindow.Zoom = 100`.
    - set `Range("A1").Select`.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
- Since we cannot run Excel, verification will rely on:
    - Code review of the VBA logic (Shape creation, event linkage).
    - Checking that proper error handling is in place.
    - User checks after re-import.
